caption: Last time, everything cold. Manny and Olgas next time.
Great pizza!
Their service has improved quite a bit lately. I always go for curbside pickup and they bring the order out promptly and put it in your car!

I was a frequent customer of this location. A few instances of a late driver here and there but last night took poor customer service to a new low! My pizza arrived yesterday with a bug in it! I called to make the issue known and was put on hold for 15 minutes. It seemed they had forgotten about me when another employee got on the phone and asked why I was calling.They failed to offer any apology or explanation. They simply said "okay, we will refund you. " That was it. I will never order from them again! I am completely disgusted!
The food is always well prepared and tasty, cashiers hands out great service. I love how neat it is and mood. Worth a try.

The thin crust pizza is delicious. I love the fact that there's just enough crust to keep each bite in tact while at the same time it's so thin that I don't feel as guilty eating a lot of it! The marble brownies are to die for!

I am very pleased with the service at Domino's pizza.  I see what is the reason why you keep many customers and many people like to buy your products.  Especially the store that is located in downtown Bethesda.  This store is the one that offers the best service.  Both the manager very attentive workers and the facilities very clean.  What one requests is provided without a pretext, I recommend it.
Fresh chicken, great people😁
Ordered through app and did carryout the employees where really friendly and the order was completed quickly. Would recommend if you want to order carry out.
Nice!

Great pizzas! I've ordered from here about 10 times and I've never gotten an order I'd consider not worth the money. Phenomenal prices for what you get since they have good deals frequently, and I'd consider Dominos the best in the business for chain pizzerias.

I called 3 times and got no answer until the last call and when I did the employee asked for my number and when I said it was going for delivery to a hotel nearby he just hung up on me. I tried calling back thinking the call dropped but I received no answer.
Fantastic and flavorful food, I liked the vibes the spot has, and the employees were friendly. Will surely visit here again.

Great customer service

This person over the phone was very polite and have good customer service skills. However, the delivery person was rude and verbalize he wanted a tip. I tried giving it to him and He refused it and saying " oh so no tip, welcome to America". First off my order was $6 bucks, delivery fee was $5 so with tax my order should have not been $17 and some change. 2nd you dont ask for a tip and not take it.... I would have given him the change out of the 20 bucks as tip  despite the costly order that was less than a quarter mile away! 3rd, this began with him calling me and telling me to get my pizza in a not so polite fashion.  So was I in the wrong for being hesitant to give the delivery person a tip?
The staff is always friendly and the Carryout area is clean. However this is my third visit to this location and the tracker says my order is ready for pick up but never is.

Awful customer service. We waited 2 1/2 hours for our pizza to never show up after they said it was on the way twice. The last phone operator to answer laughed on the phone and was very condescending. Very disappointing. We will not order from them again.

Rude on the phone, rush and cut you off. Bad customer service and dont follow through with promises. Order was made wrong but was told I would be given a credit although when i called back later to use the credit, they said they had no record. The organization and accountability is very poor at this location.

I ordered a large pizza and was given a small..... One of the slices was missing a dough piece as well! This one store has completely made me decide to never buy from dominos ever again.

Martino Wilson - Asst Manager of Dominoes in Bethesda, MD provided great customer service and delivered quality on with my order. Martino went beyond and demostrated customer service 101 best practices. I would recommend everyone / anyone to eat / buy from this location on Saint Elmo Ave. Ask for Martino. :-)

The way they make pizza affordable is by mixing a cheese blend, this pizza had more of the cheaper cheese.  For a $20 dollar large pizza I would have expected more mozzarella.  There are lots of pizza options, but they all close at 10 PM.  So when you need to get your pizza fix... this will have to do.

Totally down with the local Domino's here.  Delivery guys are always really nice and friendly, and the website is so easy to use (dangerously easy).  Extra sauce please!  Oh, delivery times are also super quick. Unlike the bobo Manny & Olgas around the corner. Forget that garbage.

It took well over an hour to receive my order.  The "order tracker" falsely stated that it had been delivered well before it actually was.  I called to check on the order status, but after 7 minutes of waiting for someone to pick up the phone I gave up.  When I Finally received my order, It was only lukewarm and I did not receive part of my order.   Someone eventually answered the phone after waiting a while on the second attempt.  I was told that I would receive a refund and the other part of my order.  I did finally receive the other part of my order after another half an hour. That portion of the order was actually hot.  But, I will not order from this store again.

I don't want to disparage the delivery drivers but the wait time tends to boarder on the obscene. I have loyally ordered from this location for the last two years, but I can no longer In good conscious order from this location again. The pizza tracker is off, the instructions are not followed, and the wait time is egregious. There were two orders that I placed in the last two months that never arrived at my door. One, I'm not certain but, I suspect was co-opted by a hungry delivery man as I ordered near closing. The other... never arrived. In all, do not order from this location.

I ordered two pizzas, when they arrived one looked like a soup that had been slammed to one side while the other was smashed. I called the store and the person answering the phone didn't listen to me, he simply kept telling me the driver was on the way. I had already received my pizzas, what was he going to do, I asked. I asked to speak to the manager who he told me was named TJ and was not there. It was only after I told the mystery phone answerer that I had taken photos of the mess and was going to post them to the corporate office that he miraculously found a manager...not TJ, Mario.  Mario agreed to send over two new pizzas without a charge, who knows if they spit in them. Seems like a shady crew working at this Dominos. Cant wait to order from Papa Johns or Pizza Hut from now on.
It is the best pizza ever!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! :)

RUDE!!!!!  The worse ever! first off the app said the food was delivered,nope took another hour for it to make it to me.  then the driver wanted to cuss me out in and argue with me that the food was cold.

I love Domino's. Like, I'd marry it if it was a person. But this location is extremely out of sync with the pizza tracker. Like extremely. Pizza was delivered to me 20 minutes after the tracker said it was delivered. Pretty bad.

Canceled my order after an hour and 20 minutes. The online tracker said it was delivered at 5:56. At 6:55 I called and was told the driver had multiple orders to deliver. I told them to cancel because last time the same thing happened and my pizza was cold. They also never bring sauce when you order things that come with it. Terrible location! I'm getting Chinese food instead.

the best,will be back again
I ordered the 2 for $5.99 deal and was disappointed. The pizza crust was way to garlicky and the steak sandwich wouldn't taste bad if the bread wasn't so burnt.....I don't think I would order again.

placed an order that claimed to have arrived at my house, when i never received the order. my card has been charged, and i haven't signed any receipts. I left my phone number and in the order comments, requested that I be called before the order was delivered. Either they lied to the system and are extremely late with my order, or they want ahead and faked a delivery, either way I am out a fair amount of money. y'all definitely just lost a customer.

Worst domino around Maryland . I personally love dominos but dislike this location so much . It always stinks, they are slow at taking and making the order . I called them 10 times from acroos the street  while the store has no costumers . Never answered . I walked to the store . There 6 ppl working all of them just talking while looking at me . After 10 minutes one comes to me asking me "you wanna order?" Then while they making my order one wearing headphones which is unsanitary and prohibited while working in a restaurant . I waited 30 minutes . They messed up my order I had to wait 20 more minutes . And they get mad at me , giving me an attitude

Some of the guys that work here are great but often times the service is pretty poor. I go to Domino's a couple times a month (at most) and order virtually the same thing every time, with some variation. Definitely don't count on them to get your order right - at least 3 out of 5 times, they'll put on the wrong toppings. I ordered Feta and PEPPERONI on a pizza and instead got some sort of lettuce/herbs on my pizza. After a long day, this pisses me off.  My 3 out of 5 star rating is overly generous because there are are a few employees I enjoy chatting with. Blah.
I have had very different experiences from here, but this location has an awesome attitude and they made the best pan pizza I've had in a while
